<TITLE> Top Nestle execs jailed over 'expired' milk </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 8 (bdnews24.com)  Senior Nestl executives, arrested after police seized 1,425 packets of "expired" Nido milk powder from a warehouse in Gulshan, were sent to jail by a Dhaka court on Wednesday. Police detained Mohammad Imtiaz, director, finance, of Nestl Bangladesh, manager Debabrata Roy Chowdhury and accounts officers Saiful Islam, Abdul Hai and Asaduzzaman after the seizure on Tuesday. Ilyas Mollah, sub-inspector of Gulshan Police Station, told bdnews24.com: "Police, on a tip-off, retrieved the out-of-date milk powder from Nestl's warehouse at House 11 of Road-18 in Gulshan." "No manufacture or expiry dates were seen on the packaging of the powder milk though there were dates on outer covers," he said. Mollah who filed a case under the Special Powers Act said Nestle officials were present during the raid. Gulshan police sub-inspector Md. Alamgir Hossain sent the arrestees to the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court Wednesday afternoon. Magistrate Abdul Majid ordered them to jail. bdnews24.
